      "content": "Subject: Budget Cap Confirmation for Project X\n\nDear [Vendor Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I am writing to confirm the budget cap for our upcoming project, Project X. As per our initial discussions, we have agreed upon a strict budget limit of $50,000. This figure has been carefully considered and approved by our finance department, and we are committed to adhering to this cap.\n\nWe value your expertise and look forward to a successful collaboration within these financial parameters. Should you have any questions or require further clarification, please do not hesitate to reach out.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\n---\n\nSubject: Re: Budget Cap Confirmation for Project X\n\nDear [Vendor Name],\n\nThank you for your prompt response. I appreciate your understanding of our budget constraints for Project X. We are confident that with your experience and our clear budget cap of $50,000, we can achieve excellent results together.\n\nPlease rest assured that we are committed to this budget limit and will not entertain any additional costs beyond this amount. We trust your professionalism and look forward to a mutually beneficial partnership.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\n---\n\nSubject: Final Confirmation on Budget Cap for Project X\n\nDear [Vendor Name],\n\nI hope this email finds you well.",
